My 2nd review: OK, I've made this desert more than a dozen times for dinners with friends and family, and have always gotten rave reviews. I've also shared the recipe with so many friends I've lost count. They all love how easy and quick it is to prepare. Thank you Jill Dupleix for sharing this with us.

Rating: 4
I have made this wonderful desert twice now. The first time I made it exactly as written, the second time I made it with orange juice. I preferred the lemon and lime rather than the orange as the lemon and lime gave it more flavor. I used a raspberry coulis drizzled on top with a couple of fresh raspberries for decoration. Definitely one of my favorite recipies.

Rating: 4
I agree with other reviewers who were skeptical, but pleased with the result! Like many others, I didn't bother with the friands, especially as I wanted a light dessert. Another cook mentioned topping with raspberries and blueberries. I don't really like blueberries, and the store didn't have raspberries, so I got blackberries, which were a really nice topping/accompaniment. Will definitely make it again!

Rating: 4
This is a delicious dessert which delivers so much great taste for so little effort. I topped each serving with whipped cream and then candied thin slices of lemon and lime which I added on top of the cream. Heavenly.

